Sure! To write an if/then statement in C, you would use the if-else statement to execute different code based on a condition. Here’s an example:

```
if (condition) {
  // Code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to execute if the condition is false
}

For example, to check if a number is even, you could use the following if-else statement:

if (number % 2 == 0) {
  printf("The number is even.");
} else {
  printf("The number is odd.");
}

To learn more about if/then statements in C, you can also check out this tutorial: https://www.tutorialspoint.com/cprogramming/c_if_else_statement.htm

